{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "rust", "icon": "VOP/rust", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rust Perforation"], "extent": [59, 80]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates a rusty, possibly perforated material."], "extent": [80, 137]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates a rusty, possibly perforated material."], "extent": [137, 201]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You will first generate a material that outputs a color, then pipe its\noutput into the Surface Color input of this operator."], "extent": [201, 327]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The rust and perforation thresholds control the contribution of each\nstage of corrosion, and represent good candidates for animation at the\nshader level if tied to Parameter operators."], "extent": [327, 513]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ") and Surface Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ") inputs are not\nconnected, the global variables by the same name will be used instead.\nTypically, you will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for\n", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and any operator that yields a lit color, such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal", "type": "link", "text": ["Shiny Metal"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal"}, " or\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, ", as inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ". If you need to access the global\nvariables directly, they are available from the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, "\noperator."], "extent": [513, 1043]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1043, 1052], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}], "extent": [1052, 1078]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}], "extent": [1078, 1102]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}], "extent": [1102, 1128]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/mold", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/mold"}], "extent": [1128, 1150]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal"}], "extent": [1150, 1179]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Rust Perforation"], "summary": ["Simulates a rusty, possibly perforated material."]}